Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.15,0:00:36.87,Lyrics eng,,0,0,0,,Never in my life I will put out this beaconing light
Comment: 0,0:00:37.07,0:00:47.96,Lyrics kanji,,0,0,0,,忘れないわあかねの朝に 誓ったことば
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.07,0:00:47.96,Lyrics romaji,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa akane no asa ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.07,0:00:41.95,Lyrics eng,,0,0,0,,The words I vowed
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.95,0:00:45.21,Lyrics eng,,0,0,0,,under the crimson daybreak
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.21,0:00:47.96,Lyrics eng,,0,0,0,,I will not misrecollect
Comment: 0,0:00:48.21,0:00:56.93,Lyrics kanji,,0,0,0,,若葉にそまる 春を呼ぼうと
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.21,0:00:56.93,Lyrics romaji,,0,0,0,,Wakaba ni somaru haru o yobou to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.21,0:00:56.93,Lyrics eng,,0,0,0,,With the voices of new leaves, the spring is summoned
Comment: 0,0:00:57.18,0:01:08.81,Lyrics kanji,,0,0,0,,斧うつひびき 道ひらくうたごえ
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.18,0:01:08.81,Lyrics romaji,,0,0,0,,Ono utsu hibiki michi hiraku utagoe
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.18,0:01:03.02,Lyrics eng,,0,0,0,,The sounds of axes chopping trees
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.02,0:01:08.81,Lyrics eng,,0,0,0,,is a song rumbling on the broad roads
Comment: 0,0:01:09.02,0:01:20.70,Lyrics kanji,,0,0,0,,こだまが胸に はずんでくるの
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.02,0:01:20.70,Lyrics romaji,,0,0,0,,Kodama ga mune ni hazunde kuru no
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.02,0:01:15.07,Lyrics eng,,0,0,0,,The chest trembles in blissful ease,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.07,0:01:20.70,Lyrics eng,,0,0,0,,echoing with mountain peaks
Comment: 0,0:01:20.95,0:01:26.54,Lyrics kanji,,0,0,0,,このおお空の 虹になりたい
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.95,0:01:26.54,Lyrics romaji,,0,0,0,,Kono oozora no niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.95,0:01:26.54,Lyrics eng,,0,0,0,,In this sky of endless blue I want to be a rainbow too
Comment: 0,0:01:26.79,0:01:36.34,Lyrics kanji,,0,0,0,,希望にとどく 虹になりたい
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.79,0:01:36.34,Lyrics romaji,,0,0,0,,Kibou ni todoku niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.79,0:01:36.34,Lyrics eng,,0,0,0,,To be reaching for the hope, I want to become a rainbow
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.06,0:01:49.04,Sign,,0,0,145,,{\blur1\b1\bord0\shad0\fade(400,400)\fs20\c&HE8DAD0&}Episode 2\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N{\fs40}Cute Fellow
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.70,0:02:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.28,0:02:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, sure. \NI'm getting up soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.32,0:02:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday we arrived in Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.99,0:02:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we spend our first night \Nsleeping in this settlement near the shore.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.59,0:02:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,With my little sister Lucy-May, I slept in the barrel because the tent was so poky.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.80,0:02:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,- Tob! Is everyone still sleeping? \N- Sleepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.88,0:03:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.01,0:03:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I have not slept enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.25,0:03:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You were the one waking me up this night!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.75,0:03:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not waking up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.81,0:03:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You were awake!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.81,0:03:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not waking up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.32,0:03:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I were awake, \Nbecause I saw such a weird animal!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.81,0:03:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It was jumping like that, \Nhop-hop, with its two legs only.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.68,0:03:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure it was not a rabbit?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.85,0:03:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course! There are no rabbits like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.86,0:03:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing, Lucy-May?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.96,0:03:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,While she was sleeping last night, \NLucy-May saw some animal that was like a giant rabbit! {'While she was sleeping' is emphasizing it could have been a dream}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.13,0:04:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It was nothing like a rabbit!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.34,0:04:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But you say it was hopping like one!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.41,0:04:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only hopping on two feet, not four.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.91,0:04:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, it should be plenty of animals \Nthat are not met in England.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.61,0:04:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Take those birds, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.38,0:04:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They look like parrots.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.75,0:04:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.39,0:04:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but could you two gather some firewood?\NWe already ran out of what was gathered yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.79,0:04:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't big sister go again?{Trying to avoid two consequtive 'Claras' here}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.18,0:04:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Clara still has a fever. \NShe would be better off getting some rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.67,0:04:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You are still quite feverish, sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.74,0:04:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Ben, moisten her forehead to cool her down.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.94,0:04:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Ben, I am fine. \NI will get up now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.58,0:04:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't exert yourself, sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.05,0:04:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, get more sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.88,0:04:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I really am such a nuisance. \NJust as we finally made it to Australia...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.36,0:04:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We still have a lot of luggage \Nto bring from the ship, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.30,0:05:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Clara, it's best that you don't worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.40,0:05:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It is so, sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.34,0:05:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.84,0:05:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Clara, get some sleep. I believe we are to face a whole bunch of challenges in the near future.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.44,0:05:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When that happens, you will have to lend your mother a helping hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.38,0:05:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So until then, \Nyou need become as healthy as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.12,0:05:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.00,0:05:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.22,0:05:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Some driftwood washed here too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.28,0:05:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.10,0:05:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. I have something to say to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.39,0:05:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.15,0:06:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,How about instead of asking me to pick it, \Nyou just put down that hamster? {Pun unintended}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.76,0:06:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But I thought \NI would let Mosh play along the seashore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.33,0:06:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Why won't you do it then?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.60,0:06:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I will right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.99,0:06:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, Mosh. \NYou are good to come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.64,0:06:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Start gathering firewood now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.71,0:06:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I am gathering.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.72,0:07:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Until later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.82,0:07:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.43,0:07:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, sis, can you take this firewood off me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.60,0:07:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You picked it up yourself, \Nbut you cannot carry it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.84,0:07:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It is because I have to collect Mosh on our way back. \NI cannot do that with firewood!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.84,0:07:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Not my concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.24,0:07:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It is John!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.45,0:07:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you two doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.32,0:07:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Gathering wood for the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.15,0:07:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Want me to help?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.18,0:07:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks. But won't you have to return to ship soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.52,0:07:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Today I'm on a furlough until noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.12,0:07:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, John, can you take this firewood?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.16,0:07:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.93,0:07:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot carry both it and Mosh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.23,0:07:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You really are such a slyboots!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.57,0:07:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you go then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.05,0:07:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Mosh, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.04,0:07:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Mosh.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.84,0:08:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,How is Clara doing, Kate?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.81,0:08:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister is having a fever again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.29,0:08:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Tob, caught something?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.77,0:08:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on. Let me take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.17,0:08:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What, a lizard? Okay, okay, \Nnow take it away from me. Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.18,0:08:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I will be visiting the ship again later.\NWe are somewhat worried about the luggage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.75,0:08:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That ship will be anchored here for another week.\NYou don't have to be hurry-scurry unloading your luggage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.27,0:08:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't mean unloading it today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.99,0:08:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Our belongings are probably piled up with the rest of cargo, \Nso I'm planning to get it all out in one big trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.76,0:08:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. That way it's the least hassle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.24,0:09:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, we brought along \Na whole prefabricated house from England.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.81,0:09:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you assembling a house here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.64,0:09:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not. \NWe are assembling it in the city of Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.67,0:09:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, you are moving that prefabricated house \Nall the way to Adelaide?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.48,0:09:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the only way we assemble it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.82,0:09:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But how are you going to move it there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.29,0:09:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,As usual — with carriages and oxcarts.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.42,0:09:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, both of those are not abundant.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.69,0:09:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I have been here before, so I know well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.43,0:09:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh well. We'll figure something.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.34,0:09:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,John...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.31,0:09:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you perchance like to have breakfast with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.24,0:09:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, but I already had one on the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.29,0:09:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, maybe just some tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.42,0:09:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's finished, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.75,0:09:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That helps a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.35,0:09:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.36,0:09:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard Miss Clara is ill again. \NMay I see her?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.37,0:10:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Sis, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.48,0:10:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,John is such a rascal!\NIn the end, he did not help me one bit!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.62,0:10:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You are still too small to understand his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.92,0:10:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,John had to go ahead \Nbecause he is worried about sister's illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.86,0:10:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I am also worried about her!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.89,0:10:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,John's worry is a special one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.00,0:10:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Why so?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.23,0:10:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to grow just a bit bigger to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.13,0:10:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you being so puffy?{'pompous' would have done better, but I want Lucy to sound more childish and besides, they previously applied a deplorable connotation to that word} You could just say John is in love with Clara and be done with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.27,0:10:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The same goes for Clara as well, is that not so?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.21,0:10:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You are growing unexpectedly fast. {Lit. 'In unexpected moments you act rather like an adult than like a child you are.'}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.89,0:10:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Clara.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.25,0:11:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that you, John?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.56,0:11:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You are still ill. Feeling better? {How do you feel?}{I don't want an irrelative rhyme here}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.73,0:11:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a small fever. No big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.09,0:11:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no small deals here, \Nwith not a single physician around.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.77,0:11:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd be glad to bring you tea \Nif you want to drink some.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.74,0:11:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want any.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.24,0:11:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What's more important, John, \Nwhen are you leaving here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.27,0:11:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.63,0:11:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.34,0:11:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you leave here, \Nwe won't meet again. Ever... {We will never meet again.}{Tryna keep drama tension up with that last word separated and emhasized}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.82,0:11:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you be able to go ashore every day until then? {Will you have everyday leaves for shore until then?}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.92,0:11:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Not every day. {Every day is not an option.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.25,0:11:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I'm just a deckhand{junior sailor}, \NI am up to my eyeballs in work.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.73,0:11:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.16,0:11:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,In just a week...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.13,0:11:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I made up my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.96,0:11:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.10,0:11:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm leaving the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.27,0:11:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Just not right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.27,0:11:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,After I return to England, I will leave for Australia at once, \Nbut this time with my little brother. {This one is somewhat a wee bit just a smidgen too much excessively redundantly outrageously wordy}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.64,0:11:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.41,0:11:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Both of our parents died. \NMy only relative is my brother. {It's just my brother and me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.01,0:12:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why the two of us will come to Australia. \NAnd then, we'll meet again!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.05,0:12:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,John...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.03,0:12:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Father is talking to Mr. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.48,0:12:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of question, Mr. Pettywell.\NThere is no way I am selling that prefabricated house.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.00,0:12:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I am willing to pony up \Ntwice the price you paid for it in England.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.24,0:12:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Twice the price?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.21,0:12:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. It's enough trees here \Nto cover all your needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.64,0:12:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,For such an artisanal{dexterous} fellow, constructing a house is a piece of cake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.78,0:12:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We will only get that prefabricated house in a few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.62,0:12:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to be living in a proper house straight away. Sleeping in a tent has already become unbearable.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.01,0:12:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How long will it take for you to assemble that house?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.99,0:12:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see, in about two weeks I should be...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.56,0:12:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No... No! Not selling it. Period.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.70,0:12:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe with some more on the table{we can make this "Yes"}...?{Damn this one is cramped}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.63,0:12:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Not happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.43,0:12:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We will assemble that house in the city of Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.50,0:12:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It is just as unbearable for us \Nto be indefinitely sleeping in tents like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.41,0:13:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll leave you with some more time to think it over.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.88,0:13:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I am not going to sell it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.16,0:13:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in such a suspense until you said you are not actually thinking of selling it. {When you actually started to consider selling it, my heart almost stopped.} {My heart went pit-a-pat when you finally said you are not actually selling it.} {God, this is one mess of a sentence}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.06,0:13:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Sell it, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.66,0:13:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Ben, as soon as we have eaten, \Nwe're going to the ship to arrange our belongings. {They specifically mean sorting luggage for future retrieval}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.13,0:13:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.14,0:13:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom said to bring along the trunk with tablecloth from Grandma.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.28,0:13:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't have any idea which trunk it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.52,0:13:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.36,0:13:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- Fetch water?\N- Fetch water?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.63,0:13:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do we go for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.13,0:14:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,A river is flowing in those woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.07,0:14:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no dangers in there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.64,0:14:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.17,0:14:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Had there been any{slightest} danger, \NI'd never send you two for mere water fetching. {She says 'something like water fetching', emphasizing that should it be a less trivial task she'd send them in even with a danger}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.84,0:14:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.74,0:14:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Just what?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.88,0:14:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Those woods are home to aborigines.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.08,0:14:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,While going to fetch water myself yesterday, \NI ran into some of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.75,0:14:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What is an aborigine?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.69,0:14:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We call that the people who lived here long before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.89,0:14:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought Australia is the place \Nno one lived in until the English turned up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.20,0:14:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Well that is not entirely so.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.00,0:14:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In Australia, you cannot even go to school or church to make the life more exciting. {In Australia, we do not even get to go to fun places like school or church.} {A long shot one: In Australia I'd even agree to go to school or church willingly.} {Note to self: rework 3 more times}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.62,0:14:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All we do is getting an errand after an errand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.98,0:14:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,True.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.14,0:14:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, imagine we meet some of those aborigines! {Hey, you think we can meet some of those aborigines?}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.19,0:14:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. {Who knows.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.99,0:14:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to meet them!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.23,0:15:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of people you imagine them?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.16,0:15:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll know when I meet them!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.76,0:15:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you gibber, \Nthey'll think you're out of your mind. {Perevodildo sure does}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.20,0:15:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,A pretty bird!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.67,0:15:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We might even run into the animal you saw last night!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.07,0:15:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That strange fellow!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.82,0:15:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.02,0:15:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.35,0:15:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You think it's an aborigine?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.92,0:15:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,An aborigine?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.76,0:15:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I am so scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.10,0:15:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What now? \NDid you not just say you want to meet one?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.20,0:15:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, it's Billy! \NAin't it Billy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.74,0:15:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Fetching water as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.48,0:15:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.48,0:15:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- Wait for us, Billy! Let's go home together! \N- Go home together!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.21,0:15:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.88,0:15:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Billy, have you seen the aborigines?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.78,0:15:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, seen them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.37,0:15:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hand it over. I'll fill it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.15,0:16:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.36,0:16:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of people are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.96,0:16:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Uhm...{Well,} The undressed kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.80,0:16:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Undressed?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.40,0:16:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.30,0:16:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, being undressed is the easiest way \Nto cope with how hot this place is. {It makes perfect sense, since being undressed is the easiest way to cope with how hot it is here.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.77,0:16:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.81,0:16:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And what else? Hey, what else is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.08,0:16:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They are rather dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.48,0:16:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Sunburnt maybe?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.11,0:16:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.61,0:16:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we rest a little, sis?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.18,0:17:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You are such a spineless one!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.21,0:17:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Say that again! {Well then...}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.75,0:17:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You really don't have to force yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.32,0:17:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I will manage! I work hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.62,0:17:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Relax, let's take a rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.69,0:17:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I am not resting!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.16,0:17:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You're such a stubborn. \NTake a rest I said!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.40,0:17:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Too tired to walk, are you, sis?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.20,0:17:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You really took it to heart! \NWe deserve a break, you kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.21,0:17:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not need to rest!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.14,0:17:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a rest!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.14,0:17:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I am not resting!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.07,0:17:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had enough of that, both of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.88,0:17:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if we will have to come all the way here \Nto fetch water every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.05,0:17:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a bit remote.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.55,0:17:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not staying in this area forever, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.26,0:17:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad said we are going to the city of Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.29,0:17:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We even brought along a prefabricated house.\NWe will carry it to Adelaide to assemble!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.67,0:17:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.90,0:17:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,One can make a small fortune \Ncatching birds here and selling them back in England.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.21,0:18:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What can that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.45,0:18:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.75,0:18:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There! See the spot where that branch splits?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.45,0:18:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,True! What is that thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.05,0:18:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is it? \NI don't see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.19,0:18:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like a bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.26,0:18:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Bear?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.33,0:18:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I see, I see! Really resembles a bear!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.27,0:18:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Bears can climb trees?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.03,0:18:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows. \NBut this one is incredibly small for a bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.10,0:18:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's catch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.91,0:18:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you plan to catch it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.87,0:18:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I will climb this tree!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.74,0:18:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Think you can climb that high?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.31,0:18:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Billy can climb it. \NHe is a boy after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.18,0:18:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you climb it, Billy?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.78,0:18:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing I can't climb...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.52,0:18:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Climb it then!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.79,0:18:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Billy, please! \NI want to catch that cute fellow!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.06,0:18:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't come back to my mother with water soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.10,0:18:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine. Forget it.{Not asking you.} I'm climbing it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.77,0:19:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, you gotta stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.71,0:19:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I sure hope it's not mordacious{/ this creature doesn't bite}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.97,0:19:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Catch it for me, Billy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.59,0:19:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.03,0:19:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,John, may I do the rowing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.26,0:19:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, be my guest. {go ahead.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.27,0:20:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry to waste your precious free time \Ntending to our trivial matters, John.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.27,0:20:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm happy to be useful. {No, it's not precious at all.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.98,0:20:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a no way! \NPlunge the oars deeper into the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.68,0:20:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.01,0:20:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Like that. Keep it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.66,0:20:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing, Billy?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.63,0:20:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he might be dead! {It appears to be dead!}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.40,0:20:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.93,0:20:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Relax, relax. Just very sleepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.90,0:20:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Then catch him quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.24,0:20:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know it's not mordacious{/ he doesn't bite}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.84,0:20:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's alright, alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.97,0:20:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the one saying that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.08,0:20:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You... have quite a cute face, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.18,0:20:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, don't bite me, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.84,0:21:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the matter, Billy? \NWhat is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.16,0:21:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you be quiet for a minute, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.60,0:21:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This fellow won't budge a bit!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.73,0:21:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what a lad! You startled me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.80,0:21:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.87,0:21:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He is adorable!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.51,0:22:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Awesome, Billy! \NNow, please be cautious not to drop this child!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.92,0:22:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's alright. He is clinging to me really tight. \NWhat an intrepid{unwavering} guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.66,0:22:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait any longer! \NHurry! Hurry! Hurry! Hurry! Hurry! Hurry!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.90,0:22:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what Kate and Co are up to.{what Kate's party is up to.} \NWhatever they are doing, it's taking them long.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.39,0:22:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, what do you intend to use him for?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.86,0:22:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Keeping!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.36,0:22:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you forget you already have Mosh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.93,0:22:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The food is not in a surplus. Not to mention dad, who would be upset at the news of you keeping such an animal!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.50,0:23:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But such a cute animal is by all means rare!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.91,0:23:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It really was so. This creature called Koala \Nwas yet another animal not met outside Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.28,0:23:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We will make sure to remember this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.15,0:23:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm definitely keeping you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.81,0:23:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He's cute, no fuss about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.31,0:24:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,To top off our tribulations, \NMr. Pettywell's black dog ran off with our meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.68,0:24:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to settle that, \Ndad quarreled with Mr. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.45,0:24:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time in Lucy-May of the Southern Rainbow: \NOddball.{Might as well be 'Replacement' in japanese but both make no sense in context of the next episode story} Join us again!
